The course aims at an extensive development of vocabulary for use in different situations. The main emphasis is on developing medical terminology both in the oral and written form. The course introduces medical vocabulary related to the following topics:
1. Bodyparts. Internal organs. Meeting the patient (personal data).
2. At the doctor's. 
3. Therapeutic exercises.
4. Anamnesis.
5. First aidObjectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at developing medical terminology through a wide variety of tasks: - reading and translating medical texts - doing vocabulary tasks - practicing grammar skillsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course the student can: * understand short and simple texts related to their future professions; * use specialized medical terminology learned during the course and apply the acquired vocabulary to their working lives; * correctly use the terminology and grammar acquired during the course; * use the acquired terminology both in oral and written form.
